data.title: Get Current Census Data for Dodge County, MN
data.meta_description: Need Dodge County demographics? Get current population, race, age, income & poverty statistics for Dodge County, MN from the US Census Bureau.
data.text:
Sources: United States Census Bureau. 2022 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates. U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey Office. Web. 7 December 2023.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2020 to July 1, 2023. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2024. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2019. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2021. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. "P2 Hispanic or Latino, and Not Hispanic or Latino by Race." 2020 Census State Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171) Summary File. U.S. Census Bureau, 2020 Census. Web. 12 August 2021. https://www.census.gov/.

Check out our FAQs for more details.

Population

With 21,088 people, Dodge County is the 48th most populated county in the state of Minnesota out of 87 counties. But watch out, Dodge County, because Martin County with 19,657 people and Waseca County with 18,981 people are right behind you.

Race & Ethnicity

The largest Dodge County racial/ethnic groups are White (90.6%) followed by Hispanic (5.1%) and Two or More (2.2%).

Median Income

In 2022, the median household income of Dodge County households was $92,890. Dodge County households made slightly more than Hennepin County households ($92,595) and Olmsted County households ($90,420) . However, 3.2% of Dodge County families live in poverty.

Median Age

The median age for Dodge County residents is 38.3 years young.
